org.eng.aisp.feature

Class FeatureGramDescriptor<WINDATA,FDATA>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eng.aisp.feature.FeatureGramDescriptor<WINDATA,FDATA>
  • Type Parameters:
    WINDATA -
    FDATA -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, IFeatureGramDescriptor<WINDATA,FDATA>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IdentityFeatureGramDescriptor

    public class FeatureGramDescriptor<WINDATA,FDATA>
extends Object
implements IFeatureGramDescriptor<WINDATA,FDATA>
    Implements the full feature extraction pipeline to produce an array of sub-features from a given IDataWindow or ILabeledDataWindow. This is a core class and generally should be used during both training and classification.

    The process involves the following distinct steps for a given IDataWindow (or ILabeledDataWindow) instance

    1. Optionally breaking the window into sub-windows defined by a window size and shift, in milliseconds.
    2. Applying a single instance of IFeatureExtractor to all sub-windows to create an array of IFeature (or ILabeledFeature) instances.
    3. Optionally applying a single IFeatureProcessor to the array of IFeature instances to produce another array of IFeature (or ILabeledFeature) instances.
    This results in an array of IFeature (or ILabeledFeature) instances. The size of this array is defined by the number of sub-windows and for each sub-window there is exactly one IFeature (or ILabeledFeature) instance.
    Author:
    dawood

      • FeatureGramDescriptor

        public FeatureGramDescriptor(int windowSizeMsec,
                             int windowShiftMsec,
                             IFeatureExtractor<WINDATA,FDATA> extractor,
                             IFeatureProcessor<FDATA> processor)
        Defines the pipeline.
        Parameters:
        windowSizeMsec - the size of the subwindows into which each labeled data window is divided into. Set to 0 to not subdivide the labeled data windows.
        windowShiftMsec - the amount of shift in time between subsequent subwindows. Typical values are windowSizeMsec or windowSizeMsec/2.
        extractor - extracts feature from an individual window.
        processor - feature processor that operations across the features from a whole window.
